        <head xml:id="la30px-aaa516-Hd1e104">Proposition 9</head>
        <p xml:id="la30px-aaa516-d1e106">
          Proposition 9
        </p>
        <p xml:id="la30px-aaa516-d1e111">
          The main prize of Christian kings, for which they work to spread the Gospel, is not, and should not be, worldly or mundane things (which are transitory and fleeting). Rather, the prize which they strive towards is the true and ultimate reign of Christ. The Christian kings occupy Christ’s place and possession in this world. Even so, what the Pope gives in terms of lands to these same kingdoms, towards the end of preaching the Gospel, is a just donation. However, this must be done without perjuring or infringing on the infidels’ rights, which are singularly theirs, and which are far from belonging to Christian kings. 
        </p>
